In addition to the above two optical quantities, there is another parameter, single-scattering phase function p(θ), which characterizes the amount of light scattered at an angle θ from the incoming direction. It is often expressed in terms of the cosine of the scattering angle θ:3∫4πp(v)dω=2π∫−11p(v)dv=1,v=cosθ.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
