				\begin{document}$$\tau =d\cdot ({\mu }_{s}+{\mu }_{a}).$$\end{document}

To measure the reflectance and the transmittance of a sample, the photomultiplier is usually used as detectors27. Theoretically, the voltage Vδ recorded by a detector is proportional to the light power Pδ incident upon it:8Vδ=KPδ.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
