				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${V}_{\delta }=K{P}_{\delta }.$$\end{document}where K is the constant proportionality, which depends on the detector characteristics. Due to the background signal V0, which occurs in all measurements and originates from noise in the system and the presence of stray light, expression (9) has to be expanded as follows:9Vδ=KPδ+V0.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
